  "text": "The Kafka consumer group rebalance protocol is implemented through multiple interconnected components across the Apache Kafka codebase. The implementation spans two primary consumer protocols: the traditional consumer rebalance and the newer Streams group rebalance.\n\nCore Rebalance Callback Handlers:\n- `StreamsRebalanceListener` (interface) in clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/StreamsRebalanceListener.java defines callbacks for Streams group task assignment changes, including onTasksRevoked, onTasksAssigned, and onAllTasksLost methods.\n- `StreamsRebalanceListenerInvoker` (class) in clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/StreamsRebalanceListenerInvoker.java encapsulates the invocation of StreamsRebalanceListener callbacks with error handling and logging.\n- `ConsumerRebalanceListenerInvoker` (class) in clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/ConsumerRebalanceListenerInvoker.java similarly handles invocation of ConsumerRebalanceListener callbacks for partition assignment changes.\n\nRebalance Data and Configuration:\n- `StreamsRebalanceData` (class) in clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/StreamsRebalanceData.java holds all data needed for Streams rebalance protocol participation, including process ID, host information, topology metadata, task assignments, and partition assignments.\n- `ConsumerRebalanceListenerMethodName` (enum) in clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/ConsumerRebalanceListenerMethodName.java provides compile-time safe references to rebalance listener method names.\n\nEvent-Driven Rebalance Communication:\n- `ConsumerRebalanceListenerCallbackNeededEvent` (class) in clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/events/ConsumerRebalanceListenerCallbackNeededEvent.java signals when the network I/O thread needs to invoke a rebalance listener callback on the application thread.\n- `ConsumerRebalanceListenerCallbackCompletedEvent` (class) in clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/events/ConsumerRebalanceListenerCallbackCompletedEvent.java notifies that a callback execution has completed, including any errors that occurred.\n\nRebalance Metrics and Monitoring:\n- `RebalanceMetricsManager` (abstract class) in clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/metrics/RebalanceMetricsManager.java is the abstract base class for rebalance protocol metrics, defining interfaces for recording rebalance start/end events.\n- `ConsumerRebalanceMetricsManager` (class) in clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/metrics/ConsumerRebalanceMetricsManager.java extends RebalanceMetricsManager to track consumer group rebalance metrics including latency, success/failure rates, and duration.\n- `ShareRebalanceMetricsManager` (class) in clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/metrics/ShareRebalanceMetricsManager.java extends RebalanceMetricsManager to track share group rebalance metrics.\n- `RebalanceCallbackMetricsManager` (class) in clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/metrics/RebalanceCallbackMetricsManager.java manages metrics specifically for rebalance callback execution latencies (partitions revoked, assigned, and lost).\n\nAll these components work together in a coordinated flow: rebalance events trigger callbacks through the invoker classes, which emit events to notify the application thread, and metrics managers track the entire process for monitoring and observability."
}

